The paper deals with the problem of solving mixed linear regression, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The proposed algorithm involves tensor decomposition and alternating minimization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these categories are closely related to the problem of mixed linear regression. Additionally, the paper involves some technical conditions and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
